          <msContents>
            <summary>Small manuscript for private use, recitation, and consultation in celebration of the fourth day of the bright half of the month of Bhādra (August/September), called Haritālika. This day is especially auspicious for the Hindu deity Śiva and his worship (pūjā). Rites of fasting and various offerings are mentioned among other rites.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
